    "We found that there were generally three types of team compositions:1.",
    "Teams composed of handpicked subject matter experts in relevant areas (e.g., national security, healthcare, law, alignment), both internally and externally sourced 2.",
    "Crowdsourced teams chosen from crowdworking platforms or attendees of a live event 3.",
    "Teams composed of language models (i.e., language models prompted or fine tuned to red-team themselves)The resources available to evaluation teams varied based on team composition.",
    "For crowdsourced teams, red-teaming efforts were time-boxed either by participant or by task, and access to models was available only through APIs [57,29]."
  ],
